name: Mallard Duck
description: The mallard is a dabbling duck that breeds throughout the temperate and subtropical Americas, Eurasia, and North Africa.
location: Found in wetlands, ponds, lakes and rivers in many parts of the world

name: Muscovy Duck
description: The Muscovy duck is a large duck native to Mexico and Central and South America.

name: Pekin Duck
description: The Pekin duck is a domesticated duck used primarily for egg and meat production.
location: Originally bred in China, now found in many parts of the world

name: Black Duck
description: The black duck is a species of dabbling duck found in North America.

name: Wood Duck
description: The wood duck is a species of duck that is found in North America.

name: Mandarin Duck
description: The Mandarin duck is a perching duck species native to East Asia.

name: Northern Pintail
description: The Northern pintail is a species of duck that breeds in the northern areas of North America, Europe, and Asia.

name: Canvasback Duck
description: The canvasback duck is a species of diving duck that is found in North America.

name: Eurasian Wigeon
description: The Eurasian wigeon is a species of dabbling duck that breeds in the northern areas of Europe and Asia.

name: Ring-necked Duck
description: The ring-necked duck is a species of diving duck that breeds in North America and winters in the southern United States, Mexico, and the Caribbean.
location: North America, southern United States, Mexico, and the Caribbean
